      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PUB CRAWL (4) had his first try here last time and wasn't as well away as normal and just never got into the race. Previous form is strong for this and well worth another chance. Same for STANDARD STREET (6) who was well off best last time when jumping to 1400m. Didn't run it out and dropped right out. On the quick back-up and the sharper trip suits. Previous ratings good for this. OUR SQUAMOSA (5) is a lightly raced filly who was good in her first campaign for the new yard. Won only try course and distance and expected to go close fresh. HIGHLANDS (1) is a former Victorian who is well placed at this level. Tricky gate but has the ability. BLACK COAL (2) is a speedy type who will take catching off the inside.",
